 Eq for a few months now wanted to start and alt.  I have a 42 driud and want to mix it up a bit, so I made a halfling warrior.  I though it would be nice to not get hit so, I put 25 pts into agi and the other 5 into str.  The warrior in only lvl 17 so I haven't had much experience with him.  The main question is am I wasting my time or should I restart?  If you think its a good idea to restart, some advise on race and where to put stats.<br>
<br>
many thanks,<br>
Kokbonck<br>
Lvl 17th warrior Tarew Marr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaldaranbladestrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galdaran Bladestrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/01 11:43:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   well</span><hr size=1> You'll still be able to be a good warrior, but your hp's will never match that of an ogre, large races also have the advantage of slam, which personnally i think is a HUGE advantage.<br>
<br>
17 lvl's is quite far in, and large races do have alot of disadvantages too - faction, size, speed... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uadexxeda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adex Xeda</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://adexxeda.tripod.com/adex_icon.jpg height=30 width=30 BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/01 12:21:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://adexxeda.tripod.com/ADEX_HEAD8.JPG height=267 width=135></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: well</span><hr size=1> ANY race makes a solid warrior.<br>
<br>
If you enjoy the character play him.<br>
<br>
Later on you'll get gear &lt;and shaman friends&gt; that will take care of any lacking stat. <p><CENTER><IMG SRC="http://adexxeda.tripod.com/nametag.jpg"></CENTER>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucorranndarklighter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corrann Darklighter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/23/01 1:11:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://24.7.174.143/pics/cdhead.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: well</span><hr size=1> coppie, your still young, and i'd recommend a trick a learned at 35.<br>
<br>
while Dual Wielding, carry a shield.  What I did was in my first set of 10 hot keys I dropped a copy of my melee2 slot and an inventory slot. I keep a shield in the inv slot at all times. (i only DW now unfortunately)<br>
<br>
During a fight, I pick up the shield from the hot key box and hold it with my cursor.  Everytime Bash comes up I quickly drop the shield into place and pickup the offhand weap, hit bash, and immediately drop the weap back in place.  Since 35, and really only since 41 or so when I haven't been fighting mobs requiring magic weaps to hit, I have bashed this way. Only in the last 3 levels or so have I had a magical shield to bash with.<br>
<br>
My skill has gone from 50 to 150 in the course of about 8 levels, so if you were to start now, you'd have no problems keeping bash nearly maxxed.  It has become very useful as it does stop runners, stuns them sometimes during combat, breaks casts by casters, etc.  <br>
<br>
but i would think having some decent agi would help with taking less hits. as i have picked up from reading here, str doesn't seem to be as huge a factor as everyone originally thought. it's important, but won't make you useless if low. I'm a 48 warrior and only have 136 str without a Wurmslayer loaded, and I hit fine and tank like a dwarf =)  I can take hits like the best of um so I wouldn't be worried, just have fun ! <br>
<br>
